        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(telegram): rich outbound — location, venue, video note, voice/buttons schemas",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nAgents using the Telegram channel could only send text messages, polls, stickers, and reactions. They had no way to send location pins, venue cards, or round video notes (видеокружки), and there was no schema advertising the existing voice message flag.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nExtends outbound Telegram capabilities to cover the most commonly needed rich content types, following the existing `sendPollTelegram`/`sendStickerTelegram` patterns without touching core.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAgents can now call three new Telegram actions:\n- **`sendLocation`** — sends a location pin with latitude/longitude and optional horizontal accuracy\n- **`sendVenue`** — sends a venue card (location + title + address + optional Foursquare/Google Place ID)\n- **`sendVideoNote`** — sends a round video note (видеокружок, up to 60 s square MP4)\n\nThe message tool schema now also advertises:\n- **`asVoice`** on `sendMessage` (was already functional but undocumented)\n- **`presentation`** with inline button structure (url / command / webApp) when `buttonsEnabled`\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send-location.test.ts` — 8 tests: happy path for location/venue, out-of-range coordinate errors, empty title/address errors\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send-video-note.test.ts` — 2 tests: empty mediaUrl guard, delegation assertion\n- `extensions/telegram/src/channel-actions.contract.test.ts` — updated expected actions list, all passing\n- All three actions wired end-to-end: `send.ts` → `action-runtime.ts` → `channel-actions.ts` → `message-action-names.ts` → `message-tool-schema.ts`\n- Final whole-branch code review: no Critical findings; all Important findings addressed before PR\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
